article.headline: Youngstown St. 95, Lock Haven 55
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Byron Davis scored 19 points and four other Penguins reached double-figures as Youngstown State grabbed an early lopsided lead to beat Lock Haven 95-55 Friday night. Youngstown State (2-1) used runs of 15-2 and 22-2 to build a 60-16 halftime lead. Thirteen Youngstown State players scored in the game as the Penguins emptied the bench in the second half. John Barber scored 13, Gemayl Johnson had 11, Vytas Sulskis scored 10 and Dan Boudler grabbed 15 rebounds while scoring 10 points for the Penguins. Billy Arre had 15 points and Denny Mortimer added 14 for Lock Haven (0-1). The Bald Eagles shot just 31 percent and were outrebounded by Youngstown State, 62-33.
